Model-based analysis for continuous data using discontinuous piecewise polynomials per calendar time

piecewise_cal_cont.Rd

Performs linear regression taking into account all trial data until the arm under study leaves the trial and adjusting for time using discontinuous piecewise polynomials in each calendar time interval

Usage

piecewise_cal_cont(
  data,
  arm,
  alpha = 0.025,
  unit_size = 25,
  ncc = TRUE,
  poly_degree = 3,
  ...
)

Arguments

data

Simulated trial data, e.g. result from the datasim_cont() function

arm

Indicator of the treatment arm under study to perform inference on (vector of length 1)

alpha

Type I error. Default=0.025

unit_size

Number of patients per calendar time unit Default=25

ncc

Boolean. Whether to include NCC data into the analysis. Default=TRUE

poly_degree

Degree of the piecewise polynomial. Default=3

...

Further arguments for simulation function

Value

List containing the p-value (one-sided), estimated treatment effect, 95% confidence interval, an indicator whether the null hypothesis was rejected or not for the investigated treatment and the fitted model

Author

Pavla Krotka

Examples


trial_data <- datasim_cont(num_arms = 3, n_arm = 100, d = c(0, 100, 250),
theta = rep(0.25, 3), lambda = rep(0.15, 4), sigma = 1, trend = "linear")

piecewise_cal_cont(data = trial_data, arm = 3)
